The safest way to get there is the raft from Oasis (bind at the dock), which goes straight to the island you want.  You don't need invis - the raft lands on a safe part of the island.<br>
<br>
Here, kill the single ogres scattered around the island.  I know of 4 - one on the rocky area near the docks to the South (watch out for The Great Oowomp nearby - he's usually camped, but if not, stay away - he *will* kill you!).  One nearby between two rocks - this one (Raider Watchman) is slightly tougher and drops stuff like rawhide pretty often, so whoever's camping Oowomp often kills this guy as well for a little profit on the side.  He also drops some watchman glasses for a nice Iksar shaman quest, those are no-drop.<br>
On the other side of the beach is another ogre, and the final one is highish up on a rock near where the raft lands on the other (North) side of the island.<br>
My technique is to go from one to another in a circle.  By the time you've killed the 4th, the 1st and 2nd are back up.<br>
<br>
Don't bother with the ones in/by the huts.  1) Oowomp is sometimes there 2) I'm pretty sure they'll mob you<br>
<br>
The EXP is *tremendous* from 20-22.  As in, the only better EXP I've known is the Hermit in SK, and he's always camped by someone else anyways.  <br>
At 22 it slows down a little, but *still* excellent.   I haven't timed it, but this mage seems to have gone from 20-23 in no time (8-10 hours maybe?  If that.  Haven't timed it, but it's *fast*)<br>
At 23, some of them are light blue cons, and the EXP slows down considerably.  By 24 I'd move on.  But 20-22 is amazingly fast.<br>
<br>
The Wise Ones are casters, but with low HP making them very easy to kill.  Kill them fast - they can root etc - but don't worry about attacking them, as for casters they're very weak.<br>
<br>
Use the EARTH pet.  These guys run when weakened, sometimes rather fast, and I know at least the Watchman runs towards the huts to fetch some buddies when he's weak (found out the hard way).  Get em rooted.<br>
<br>
I wouldn't have tried this with the level 16 pet - I think they're too weak.  So come here at 20.<br>
<br>
Med up to full for the one between the rocks, and perhaps the one high up on the rock near the raft.  Both tend to hit hard, and so need extra nuking to keep your pet in good health.  The others, I've found, can be tackled with 2-3 bars of mana (2 bolts of flame) if you want to outdamage the pet and get full XP, or even less otherwise.<br>
<br>
Oh, and don't bother with throwing daggers if you often use them to pull... hehe... these guys have a larger agro radius than your throwing range, so it's pointless <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     <br>
<br>
The only faction on these guys is Venril Sathir (gets worse) which, as far as I know, is only the evil outpost in Overthere.  Since good guys are KoS there anyway, it makes no difference.<br>
<br>
Loot is variable, totally.  Some days all you get is a bit of change and some rations/booze.  Other days you get a plat in change per kill every time, and almost always some fine steel or rawhide.  The good days tend to make up for the bad ones...<br>
<br>
This is best if you're the only one there.  It really slows down when you get another person doing this camp, although it doesn't happen often - but if it does, grab the bloated belly to Overthere and hunt the stuff there for a bit by the beach or mud pit.  If you're a good race, you have to catch the ship by swimming onto it, or perhaps invis up the docks.  Then at overthere, jump off before the docks - even with invis, as there are undead guards at this dock.  Swim to shore, and don't go inside the outpost.  No problem at all.<br>
<br>
Definitely good for 20-22.  Level 23 is a little slower, but still  nice. <p>--&nbsp;<br>
